OL,3,CCollecting the dead with nowhere to
OL,4,Cflee: The reality for those left in
OL,5,CRafah
OL,7,FThe siren blasting from his fire
OL,8,Fengine suggests he is rushing to help
OL,9,Fthe injured, but, all too often these
OL,10,Fdays, he is going to collect the dead.
OL,12,FThere is little life left in Rafah
OL,13,Fnow. Outside a makeshift mortuary,
OL,14,Fpeople pull up in cars with their
OL,15,Fboots filled with bodies.
OL,17,FThey work together to lift and lower
OL,18,Fthem carefully into plastic body bags.
OL,19,FIt is up to the living to try and
OL,20,Fprovide whatever dignity they can for
OL,21,Fthe dead.
