OL,3,CCollecting the dead with nowhere to
OL,4,Cflee: The reality for those left in
OL,5,CRafah
OL,7,F"We are suffocating now, we can't
OL,8,Fbreathe. We've had fire dropped on us.
OL,9,Fartillery dropped on us. It's
OL,10,Fgenocide. Where shall we go?" He asks.
OL,11,F"To the sea?"
OL,13,FFamilies that have made it to other
OL,14,Fcities are now faced, once again, with
OL,15,Ftrying to set up their lives in
OL,16,Fwhatever bombed or burnt out buildings
OL,17,Fthey can find.
